Comment: 0,0:03:42.04,0:03:42.04,Default,[chapter],0,0,0,,{TIME:222040,222040}Part A
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.41,0:03:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:222416,224501}Wake up, Martin.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.50,0:03:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:224501,225836}What are you\Nscreaming for, man?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.83,0:03:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:225836,229339}Sir, I brought you a letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.26,0:03:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:235262,237014}Please read it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.18,0:04:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:242186,246940}Let's meet tomorrow at the\NBritish Museum library.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.69,0:04:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:247691,249568}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.56,0:04:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:249568,251570}You're uh… of Paris…\NWhat's your name again?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.57,0:04:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:251570,252905}Isabelle.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.90,0:04:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:252905,256700}Ah, yes.\NHere's to Isabelle from Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.70,0:04:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:256700,258785}A toast to Isabelle from Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.78,0:04:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:258785,260746}Cheers!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.74,0:04:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:260746,261955}Cheers!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.38,0:04:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:275385,276386}You got a problem, buddy?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.38,0:04:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:276386,279181}It's that monster!\NHe chased us all the way here!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.01,0:04:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:282017,286188}This is a place of rest.\NPlease, come over some other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.86,0:04:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:293862,295697}You bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.32,0:05:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:300327,303163}Wait. If you want to make trouble,\Ntake it outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.04,0:05:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:305040,308627}Here, it's on the house. But after\Nyou finish, I must ask you to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.38,0:05:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:316385,319137}Hey, buddy.\NWe're Englishmen, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.13,0:05:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:319137,321974}Our ancestors wreaked\Nhavoc on the Seven Seas.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.97,0:05:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:321974,324559}Believe me, you don't\Nwant to mess with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.44,0:05:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:334444,336321}I was asking you politely.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.32,0:05:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:336321,338198}He's mocking us!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.19,0:05:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:338198,340450}– Let's get him!\N– Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.17,0:06:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:356174,360053}If you chose not to\Nlisten to reason, so be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.05,0:06:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:360053,364558}The people who bring violence to our\Nbeloved pub, we call them garbage.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.55,0:06:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:364558,367894}And we deal with garbage\Nin a very simple manner.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.45,0:06:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:382451,384286}All right, gentlemen,\Nback to drinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.28,0:06:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:384286,386913}Don't sweat it.\NThese are just a few scratches.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.91,0:06:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:386913,389249}To cheer you up,\Neveryone gets a free beer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.67,0:06:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:393670,397215}Incredible! I didn't know that\Ntaverns had such contraptions!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.67,0:06:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:397674,400677}You see, we British\Nlove our machines.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.63,0:06:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:401636,404556}A bit off topic, do you know\Nwhere to stay for the night?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.55,0:06:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:404556,409603}No. We are in London for the first time\Nand we cannot tell left from right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.60,0:06:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:409603,412981}No problem. I will introduce you\Nto someone you can trust.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.81,0:06:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:415817,418278}They have very good food there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.27,0:07:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:418278,421156}Especially roasted beef and puddings.\NThey melt in your mouth!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.53,0:07:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:425535,430165}I just don't know if it will suit\Nyour sophisticated French tastes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.21,0:07:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:437214,438757}Jean, that…\Ncan't be him, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.01,0:07:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:449017,450268}Run for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.26,0:07:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:450268,452270}I see he doesn't know\Nwhen to let go.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.73,0:07:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:454731,458318}No! Bullets don't work on him.\NWe have to run!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.69,0:07:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:462697,463949}Impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.86,0:07:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:467869,469830}Hurry! We have to run!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.67,0:08:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:481675,483552}Isabelle! We're running away!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.63,0:08:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:526636,528555}I think we lost him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.55,0:08:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:528555,533435}Jean, I can't go on anymore.\NI'm sick of all this running.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.43,0:08:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:533435,535520}I want to go back to Versailles.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.52,0:08:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:535520,537689}You think I don't?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.68,0:09:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:537689,542777}I got tangled up in things I don't fully\Nunderstand and at times, I regret it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.77,0:09:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:542777,546740}Do you reckon we could just\Nstraight up apologize and come back?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.74,0:09:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:546740,549117}You know full well\Nit won't work, Isabelle.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.11,0:09:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:549117,552829}We both got involved in it\Non our own accord.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.82,0:09:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:552829,556708}You are no longer Isabelle Rostain\Nor Isabelle from Versailles.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.70,0:09:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:556708,559085}You are Isabelle from Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.08,0:09:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:559085,560754}Isabelle… from Paris?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.75,0:09:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:560754,563548}Yes. Isabelle from Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.84,0:09:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:567844,570263}I am Isabelle from Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.76,0:09:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:570764,576478}As long as I liveth, i shalt protect\Nthe freedom and people of Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.47,0:09:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:576478,578480}Long live Isabelle!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.48,0:09:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:578480,581816}Isabelle is our savior!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.81,0:09:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:581816,584569}Praise Isabelle from Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.90,0:09:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:585904,587906}So much fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.90,0:09:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:587906,590075}Isabelle from Paris\Nand Jean from Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.07,0:09:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:590075,592619}Paris of Isabelle.\NParis of Jean.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.61,0:09:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:592619,595372}Sounds like a title\Nof a novel, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.58,0:10:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:599584,600835}Do you regret leaving?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.04,0:10:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:603046,608051}The floor may be a bit hard here,\Nbut we should catch some sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.05,0:10:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:608051,611096}Tomorrow we will go on\Nanother great adventure.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.72,0:10:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:612722,614558}Good night.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.10,0:11:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:659102,660895}The situation is this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.89,0:11:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:660895,664357}Isabelle made contact\Nwith the British revolutionaries.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.35,0:11:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:664357,670071}Therefore, we must dispose not only of her,\Nbut also everyone who talked to her!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.07,0:11:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:670071,673575}Gather everyone\Nand don't spare anyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.57,0:11:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:673575,675118}Panza!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.36,0:11:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:675368,678913}I told you to leave the girl alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.41,0:11:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:679414,681291}Who… Who's there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.04,0:11:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:684044,686421}Close the door!\NDon't let anyone leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.42,0:11:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:686421,688423}Show yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.42,0:11:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:688423,690800}I don't hide from anyone.\NI am over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.76,0:11:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:691760,693928}Count Red?\NHow did you get here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.92,0:11:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:693928,696264}Why are you opposing us?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.26,0:11:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:696264,701186}Count Red doesn't have to answer\Nthe questions of cowards like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.18,0:11:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:701186,704147}You deserve only to be wiped off\Nthe face of the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.14,0:11:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:704147,705982}What is it?\NWhat's that sound!?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.98,0:11:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:705982,709444}In a moment or two, all that's left\Nfrom your boat will be a few splinters.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.48,0:11:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:712489,716618}Damn, it's a bomb!\NWithdraw! Withdraw!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.61,0:11:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:716618,718495}It's a bomb!\NSave yourselves!
Comment: 0,0:12:12.42,0:12:12.42,Default,[chapter],0,0,0,,{TIME:732425,732425}Part B
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.42,0:12:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:736429,738973}Leave the boat!\NLeave the boat!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.39,0:12:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:747399,749192}Shoot! Shoot!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.19,0:12:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:749192,751528}Kill him! Kill him!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.39,0:13:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:782392,784018}Are you all right, Irma?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.97,0:13:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:784978,786229}I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.22,0:13:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:786229,787647}You won't run away from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.64,0:13:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:787647,790817}I don't want anyone's help.\NI'll get rid of this rodent myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.94,0:13:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:793945,795739}Don't put yourself\Nin danger, Irma.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.15,0:13:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:834152,835820}Say your prayers.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.82,0:13:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:835820,837447}Hey, boss!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.32,0:14:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:838323,841075}They're our men.\NGo without me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.07,0:14:02.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:841075,842911}I'm not important.\NSave yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.32,0:14:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:843328,846706}You're the only one I don't want\Nto lose. Get outta here!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.79,0:14:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:855799,857258}You're pretty good!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.92,0:14:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:857926,860804}You too. You're doing\Nsurprisingly well for a coward.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.80,0:14:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:860804,862764}Watch your words, dog!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.78,0:14:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:880782,884244}That would be it, you red clown.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.70,0:14:51.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:888706,891459}The fire has spread.\NThe boat is about to explode!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.91,0:14:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:891918,893086}What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.96,0:14:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:893962,895630}Finally. How long\Ndid I have to wait?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.42,0:15:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:901427,902804}Until next time!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.80,0:15:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:902804,905098}Next time, I will squeeze\Nthe life out of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.51,0:15:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:905515,906891}I look forward to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.76,0:15:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:909769,913314}{\i1}Wait a second.\NI heard that voice somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.31,0:15:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:913314,915483}{\i1}Whose voice it is? Whose?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.90,0:15:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:915900,917944}{\i1}Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.94,0:15:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:917944,922156}{\i1}The Count Red's voice\Nsounded strangely familiar.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.15,0:15:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:922156,928204}{\i1}Panza, however, could not\Nremember at all who it belonged to.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.75,0:15:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:934752,939841}{\i1}Meanwhile Victor, worried\Nabout the fate of our heroine,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.84,0:15:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:939841,942927}{\i1}learned from Thiers\NIsabelle's whereabouts,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.92,0:15:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:942927,945972}{\i1}and was slowly\Napproaching London.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.72,0:15:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:947724,950059}{\i1}They want Isabelle dead or alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.05,0:15:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:950059,953062}{\i1}What could a fifteen-year-old\Ngirl do to them?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.06,0:15:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:953062,955064}{\i1}Thiers has lost his mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.06,0:15:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:955064,957066}{\i1}God help you, Isabelle.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.40,0:16:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:964407,966159}{\i1}Don't look at it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.75,0:16:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:973750,978129}{\i1}Seeing the portrait of Isabelle,\NVictor got flooded with memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.12,0:16:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:978129,982717}{\i1}Isabelle's face reminded him\Nof her sister, Geneviève.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.59,0:16:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:985595,987347}British Museum.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.34,0:16:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:987347,992060}The largest museum in the world,\Nlocated at Russell Square in London.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.06,0:16:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:992060,997357}From Ancient Egypt, through Greece,\NRome, India, to China and Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.35,0:16:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:997357,1004614}{\fscx95}The collections contain works of art, exhibits\Nfrom excavations, folk crafts and much more.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.61,0:16:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1004614,1007283}We're in for some nice views.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.28,0:16:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1007283,1010954}How can you be so calm in these\Ncircumstances and think about the views?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.24,0:16:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1011245,1014540}Shh! Calm down, or else\Nyou'll look suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.33,0:17:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1018336,1020463}That's their idea of a disguise?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.46,0:17:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1020463,1023383}In the end they're only kids.\NAfter them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.17,0:17:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1024175,1030348}The British Museum Library\Ncan boast 8 million volumes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.34,0:17:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1030348,1034769}The spectacular reading room can easily\Naccommodate over a hundred book lovers.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.43,0:17:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1036437,1037647}Interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.78,0:17:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1046781,1049951}Sit down, please.\NPretend that you are reading a book.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.70,0:17:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1051703,1053788}I understand Jules' request.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.78,0:17:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1053788,1057083}This morning, 120 of our\Npoliticians and military experts
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.08,0:17:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1057083,1062505}set off for Paris\Nto help defend the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.50,0:17:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1062505,1065717}I don't know how many of them\Nwill actually make it there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.71,0:17:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1065717,1068594}This is all we could do.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.80,0:17:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1068803,1070805}Give this to Jules.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.80,0:17:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1070805,1073141}It contains the names\Nof everyone we sent.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.14,0:17:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1073141,1076519}Keep this list safe,\NIsabelle. Now go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.51,0:18:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1076519,1082275}Your actions will go down in history\Nas catalysts of wonderful changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.27,0:18:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1082275,1085403}I'm just helping my sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.73,0:18:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1085737,1088990}A man always acts\Nfor his loved ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.99,0:18:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1088990,1091242}That's where it all starts.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.03,0:18:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1092035,1094746}Goodbye, Isabelle.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.58,0:18:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1095580,1098124}Thank you very much, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.04,0:18:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1103046,1107341}{\i1}The city that is protected\Nand ruled only by its citizens.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.34,0:18:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1107341,1109135}{\i1}What a noble idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.13,0:18:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1109135,1111512}{\i1}However, it is still too early.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.51,0:18:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1111512,1117060}{\i1}I hope that the dream of the people of Paris\Nwill be more than just an idealistic fantasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.61,0:18:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1130615,1132283}Isabelle!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.11,0:18:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1133117,1134243}Jean, he's got the letter!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.24,0:18:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1134243,1135745}What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.99,0:18:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1136996,1138706}Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.74,0:19:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1139749,1141459}He'll escape us!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.54,0:19:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1148549,1150968}I was waiting for you, Isabelle.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.05,0:19:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1155056,1156641}It is time to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.06,0:19:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1162063,1163564}Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.60,0:19:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1165608,1166818}Isabelle, catch!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.61,0:19:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1167610,1169070}Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.28,0:19:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1173282,1174742}Not another step.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.78,0:20:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1215783,1216784}We can do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.78,0:20:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1216784,1218161}All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.16,0:20:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1218161,1220371}I admit that you\Nsurprised me, brats.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.95,0:20:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1220955,1224458}I am afraid, however, that\Nyour fencing show ends here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.50,0:20:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1232508,1235636}{\i1}All or nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.60,0:20:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1248608,1252278}Boss! It's the London police!\NThe police is gonna come any second!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.52,0:20:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1252528,1256157}What? Damn it!\NEveryone, retreat!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.82,0:21:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1257825,1261245}You're bloody lucky, you squirts.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.24,0:21:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1261245,1263247}Withdraw!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.66,0:21:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1265666,1268336}Ms. Isabelle,\NI have your letter here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.33,0:21:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1268336,1270171}Gaston!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.17,0:21:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1270171,1272590}I've arranged for us\Na ship to France.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.59,0:21:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1272590,1275218}They'll be waiting on\Nthe Waterloo Bridge at 7 o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.21,0:21:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1275218,1277803}The police will be here soon.\NFollow me, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.59,0:21:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1278596,1280014}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.93,0:21:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1285937,1288356}Ah, it must be them!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.35,0:21:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1288356,1290399}That's our ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.73,0:21:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1296739,1298449}Oh, no! It's him again!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.95,0:21:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1300952,1303704}Will he ever learn to let go?\NI'm so sick of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.70,0:21:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1303704,1305414}Time to end this,\Nonce and for all.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.41,0:21:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1305414,1307875}Jean, don't be ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.87,0:21:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1307875,1310962}Let's see who is stronger here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.96,0:21:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1310962,1314799}Okay, Karlov! I'm yours!\NShow me what you can do!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.01,0:22:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1324016,1325226}Jean!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.06,0:22:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1328062,1330106}Jean, are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.06,0:22:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1332066,1333109}Jean!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.10,0:22:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1333109,1334485}Jean!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.20,0:22:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1350209,1352169}Victor! It's Victor!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.38,0:22:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1356382,1359885}Where did he come from?\NIt's not funny anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.92,0:22:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1360928,1363889}Isabelle, forget everything\Nthat has happened so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.88,0:22:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1363889,1366434}I'll take care of Thiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.43,0:22:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1366434,1368561}You two just go back\Nto Versailles safely.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.56,0:22:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1368561,1371355}Victor, but I…
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.35,0:22:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1371355,1376402}You came to London on a trip.\NThat is all. Understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.73,0:23:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1376736,1380489}No matter what happens\Nin Paris or the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.48,0:23:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1380489,1383826}I just want you to lead\Na peaceful and happy life.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.54,0:23:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1390541,1392376}{\i1}Victor…
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.71,0:23:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1392710,1400968}{\i1}Isabelle heard a declaration\Nof love in Victor's words.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.96,0:23:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1400968,1404930}{\i1}"I finally caught his eye."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.93,0:23:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1404930,1412438}{\i1}In Isabelle's heart,\NParis, Geneviève,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.43,0:23:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1412438,1416859}{\i1}the dangerous trip\Nto London, everything…
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.85,0:23:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1416859,1420196}{\i1}became shrouded in a thick fog.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.19,0:23:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1420196,1423532}{\i1}Isabelle was happy now.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.91,0:23:57.88,Credits,[credits],0,0,0,,{TIME:1433918,1437880}{\fad(400,400)\c&HFAFAFA&\blur0.7\fs17\an5\pos(496,373)\t(1904,3904,5,\c&H101010&)}To be continued
Comment: 0,0:23:58.08,0:23:58.08,Default,[chapter],0,0,0,,{TIME:1438089,1438089}Preview
